      • setPhoneNumber

        public void setPhoneNumber(java.lang.String phoneNumber)
        Sets the phone number of a customer. Inputed string is processed so prefix for Denmark is erased if it's present, spaces are deleted and the resulting string is checked if it consists only of 8 digits. Otherwise exception for illegal argument is thrown
        Parameters:
        phoneNumber - the phone number of a customer as a String

      • setEmailAddress

        public void setEmailAddress(java.lang.String emailAddress)
        Sets the email address of a customer. Inputed string is not a valid email address if '@' (at sign) is the first letter, the last letter or isn't in the sting at all. In one or more of these cases, the exception for illegal argument is thrown.
        Parameters:
        emailAddress - The email address of a customer as a String
